’Ł@3917ee14f3e0cb8b66a4c2f1b3b785dbf250adc3f181a0209d3b05897c701a5fŚoTitle: title: encode base64
Path: Examples
Content:
Encode a string with Base64
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> "Alphabet from A to Z" | encode base64
QWxwaGFiZXQgZnJvbSBBIHRvIFo=

```
Encode arbitrary data
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 0x[BE EE FF] | encode base64
vu7/

```
Use a URL-safe alphabet
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 0x[BE EE FF] | encode base64 --url
vu7_

```
’Ł@cd61c3c79364a32559d95af76778ac4a38285a8b88df13aee20a0d4f38c18772ŁøTitle: title: encode base64
Path: Notes
Content:
The default alphabet is taken from RFC 4648, section 4.  A URL-safe version is available.
Note this command will collect stream input.
